<P>
   GM-FIAT (London) _ General Motors, the world's largest carmaker,
and Fiat, Italy's largest industrial company, are poised to
announce an alliance that will include a share swap. Also, Fiat is
considering bidding for the Volvo truck business. By Andrew Ross
Sorkin and Keith Bradsher.
</P>
<P>
   JOY-CONCERNS (Undated) _ Bill Joy, a Sun Microsystems founder
and unofficial spokesman for Silicon Valley techies, has become a
little worried about the future. In a 20,000-word article, to be
published in Wired as an open letter to the technology industry,
Joy says that nanotechnology and biotechnology pose significant
dangers to mankind and must be closely monitored. Here's an account
of what keeps Joy awake at night _ and what others have to say
about his missive. By John Markoff.
