<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MOVIE-VIDEOS-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
PROVIDENCE GETS ON THE MAP; INTOLERANCE AS ARCHITECTURE 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.2000 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES: ``Outside Providence'' _ Director Michael Corrente
is doing for Providence what Barry Levinson did for Baltimore.
While this well-done film garnered the lion's share of its
publicity because Alec Baldwin gained a few pounds, it's better
than that.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Architecture of Doom'' (DVD) _ This is one of the best
documentaries to come along in a while. The merging of art,
politics, and murder under the Nazis is tragically and compellingly
detailed in this gripping story of how racism and intolerance were
manifest in the Hitler-ordered architecture of the time.
</P>
<P>
   ``Scooby-Doo Meets the Boo Brothers'' _ There are some great
cartoon characters, such as Daffy Duck and Bullwinkle J. Moose, but
I don't get Scooby-Doo. But he's very popular. I must admit I hit
the fast-forward button on this DVD, but I presume Scooby fans will
scoot right out for this one.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   DVD NEWS: In mid-May, Columbia Tristar is having a sale on
previously overpriced titles. Local movie fans might get a kick out
of ``Dead Heat on a Merry-Go-Round'' with James Coburn as con man
Eli Koch for $19.95. The 1966 release was primarily shot on
location in Boston and features some great shots of the city. It
also features the screen debut of Harrison Ford, as a bellboy.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS: March 21: ``Jakob the Liar'' (American
version; on DVD), ``Pokemon: The First Movie,'' ``The Limey,''
``Endurance,'' ``Whiteboyz,'' ``Horror Express'' (DVD), ``Velocity
Trap'' (DVD), ``Swing.'' March 28: ``The Sixth Sense,'' ``Crazy in
Alabama,'' ``Joseph and the Amazing Technicolor Dreamcoat,''
``Voices From a Locked Room,'' ``The Magnificent Seven'' (1998).
April 4: ``Star Wars: Episode I _ The Phantom Menace,'' ``Boys
Don't Cry,'' ``For Love of the Game'' (DVD), ``The Messenger: The
Story of Joan of Arc.'' April 11: ``Thugs.'' April 18: ``Mumford,''
``House on Haunted Hill,'' ``My Date With the President's
Daughter,'' ``End of Days,'' ``That's the Way I Like It,'' ``Love
Kills.'' April 25: ``Fight Club,'' ``RKO 281,'' ``Iris Blond,''
``Flawless,'' ``Music of the Heart.'' May 2: ``Dogma.'' May 9:
``Bringing Out the Dead.'' May 16: ``The World Is Not Enough''
(DVD).
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-03-13-00 1328EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
