<P>
   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN (Washington) _ Vice President Gore has challenged
Gov. George W. Bush to twice-weekly debates from now until Election
Day, surely too much of a good thing. There's a catch, of course.
Gore's offer was conditioned on Bush's agreement to abandon those
30-and 60-second attack ads. Bush isn't biting; he loves those ads
and he is not keen on debating Gore, a master of the form. Pushing
the idea can make Gore look aggressive and Bush defensive, but
keeping it up until November might drive us all nuts. By MARIANNE
MEANS.
</P>
</TEXT>
