<P>
   FLORIDA-PREZ _ Florida's primary on Tuesday is but window
dressing, but some leading pols want to make sure that doesn't
happen in the future. They're kicking around several ideas, ranging
from five regional primaries to a series of five primaries based on
the sizes of the states, from the smallest 10 (which would allow
New Hampshire to go first) to the largest 10, a primary that would
ultimately decide the party choices. (Crowley, Palm Beach Post).
14-16.
