</P>
<P>
   The New York Times News Service is planning an expanded weather
package, with a planned starting date of Monday, March 20, which
will be transmitted on Sunday, March 19. The package, consisting of
a weather map as a graphics file and a text file to accompany the
map, is available to graphics clients of the News Service. The new
map grows to 4 columns in width (52 picas), from 3, and is 6 inches
deep; the old was 4 inches deep. This new size permits the
insertion of cloud cover information and the addition of many new
cities.
</P>
<P>
   The map is available both in color and in black and white.
Because the map is much more detailed, we have devised an entirely
new palette of colors to make it easier to read the added
information. A sample of the new map is available at Wieck,
Newscom, Presslink and AP's GraphicsNet.
