<P>
   MARTIANS: COMING SOON TO A SCREEN NEAR YOU &QL;
</P>
<P>
   `MARS-FEVER'-ECONOMIST _ Hollywood is going out of this world.
On March 10, ``Mission to Mars,'' the first of several forthcoming
Martian movies, opened in cinemas across America. For the growing
``Mars advocacy'' movement, these movies are more than mere
entertainment. They are also a valuable opportunity to capitalize
on public interest in all things Martian to raise support _ and
cash _ for exploration of the red planet itself. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   `YOU DON'T HAVE TO LIKE ME ...'
</P>
<P>
   MONICA-LEWINSKY-WEIGHT-BATTLE-NYTSF _ Where did Monica Lewinsky
go? Apart from her tete-a-tete with Barbara Walters last March and
her star turn on Kenneth Starr's witness stand, Lewinsky mostly
kept to herself in the months after her affair with Bill Clinton
became public. Then, in late December, she announced her new role
as spokeswoman for the Jenny Craig weight-loss program. In this
interview, Lewinsky talks about her lifelong battle with an
unhealthy body image, the lessons she learned from her relationship
with the president, her feelings about Linda Tripp and her take on
how she will be remembered in history. By Debra Birnbaum. WITH
PHOTO. (North American rights only.) CAN BE PUBLISHED ON MARCH 16,
2000, OR ANYTIME THEREAFTER.
</P>
