   THE PRICE of `FREEDOM' &QL;
</P>
<P>
   MYTH-JOB-INDEPENDENCE-NYTSF _ In the much-hyped,
much-romanticized free-agent nation, workers are liberated from
routines, dress codes and office politics. As well as benefits,
vacations and regular paychecks. So where's the advantage? By Nina
Munk.
</P>
