</P>
<P>
   MAP-OF-TONGUE-NYTSF _ Take a thrilling journey to the inner
reaches of the mouth in search of the elusive taste receptor.
Investigate rumors that these highly specialized nerve cells, which
transmit chemical information to the brain, show up in greater
numbers and densities in some mouths. By Eric Haseltine. (Free to
clients of the NYTSF Discover package.) WITH PHOTO.
</P>
<P>
   GENERATION RX &QL;
</P>
<P>
   RITALIN-CENTERPIECE-NYTSF _ Prescribing psychotropic medications
for school-age children is a booming business these days. Ritalin's
production alone is up 700 percent since 1990. A battle has arisen
between the pro-medication and anti-medication camps: heated,
public and utterly spurious. Some children need medication; others
don't. The real trouble lies in how the assessment is made. The
person with the cash, the power and even the transportation usually
gets to identify the patient, setting the stage for all subsequent
decisions. By Amy Bloom. Also moved in ``c'' news file.
</P>
<P>
   INTERNATIONAL (moved in the ``i'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   FLIGHT OF THE LAMA &QL;
</P>
<P>
   LAMA-CENTERPIECE-NYTSF _ Dodging spies and Chinese army
checkpoints, scaling mountains in the cold, dark night, without
provisions, traveling via a Mitsubishi SUV, helicopter and
horseback, Ugyen Trinley Dorje _ the 17th Karmapa _ an appealing
14-year-old child, escaped into India. Arriving half-starved at
Dharamsala, the exile home of the Dalai Lama, he touched off a
worldwide sensation and speculation by many that he will be the
future leader of the 100,000 exiled Tibetans, the potential
temporal successor to the exiled ruler of Tibet. By Isabel Hilton.
Also moved in ``c'' news file.
</P>
<P>
   GERMAN GENDER-BENDERS: BREAKING THE POLITICAL GLASS CEILING &QL;
</P>
<P>
   `FRAU'-POLITICS-ECONOMIST _ For now, there is only one serious
candidate left in the running for the leadership of Germany's
Christian Democratic Union. After the withdrawal on March 5 of
Volker Ruhe, Angela Merkel, the party's general secretary, has
become the hot favorite among the rank and file. But in the eyes of
the CDU leadership and of its conservative Bavarian sister party,
Merkel suffers from two grave drawbacks: she comes from the former
communist east, and _ god forbid _ she is a woman. &QL;
</P>
