<P>
   THE CHANGING OFFICE: FROM FEUDALISM TO FAMILY &QL;
</P>
<P>
   OFFICE-OLD-NEW-NYTSF _ In the old days, offices operated on the
feudal system. There was the boss, or liege lord, who occasionally
dispensed favors _ raises, that is _ but more often withheld them.
For his gaze to fall upon you was supposed to be reward enough.
There were the knights, and beneath them the courtiers _ the
toadies and rumormongers and ladies-in-waiting. Everyone knew his
or her place. But the office is now a family, a home away from
home, where communication is almost constant and meanness and
hurtfulness are frowned upon. By Charles McGrath.
</P>
