Wis. Some companies even pay money to those who come in and fill
out job applications. So it follows that workers should be hopping
from job to job, taking advantage of this ``employee's market,''
demanding more perks and lures, boosting their income to the max.
But people aren't behaving that way. The job-turnover rate has been
dropping even as the unemployment rate has plunged. By David
Brooks.
