<HEADLINE>
WINE OF THE WEEK 

</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  (For release Friday, March 17) 
 
By MICHAEL LONSFORD 
c. 2000 Houston Chronicle 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Today is St. Patrick's Day, of course, but it's also the 81st
anniversary of the birth of legendary singer Nat ``King'' Cole.
Where was Cole born? &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   One of this week's featured wine's aromatic qualities is a
definite dusty, ``Ramblin' Rose'' nuance. But it's the raspberry
fruit on the palate that makes the  &UR;  &LR; 1997 Ravenswood ``Napa
Valley'' Zinfandel _ 4 1/2 stars _ so ``Unforgettable.''
</P>
<P>
   The $15.99 price tag is quite reasonable for a wine of this
quality, too, which means you won't have to hock your ``Mona Lisa''
to indulge in a bottle or two.
</P>
<P>
   Cole was born in Montgomery, Ala.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
