   FOOTBALL/NFL
</P>
<P>
   FBN-MARINO-RETIRES _ MIAMI _ Dan Marino retires after 17 years
as the quarterback of the Miami Dolphins. (Woods, Palm Beach Post).
40.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: A separate Palm Beach Post budget of sidebars and charts
was e-mailed to Sports editors.
</P>
<P>
   BASEBALL
</P>
<P>
   BBN-BRAVES _ Although he became the team's most dominant pitcher
during the playoffs last season, Kevin Millwood entered spring
training realizing that he would return to his place in the
rotation behind Greg Maddux, Tom Glavine and John Smoltz. But
Smoltz's elbow injury has forced Millwood to take a different
approach in preparation for the 2000 season. Now, he's technically
one of the Braves' ``Big Three''. How has Millwood changed entering
the season? (CRogers, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 20.
</P>
<P>
   BASKETBALL/NCAA
</P>
<P>
   BKN-SEAN-ELLIOTT _ It was less than eight months ago that Sean
Elliott had kidney transplant surgery. At that time, it was
doubtful that he would play basketball again. Tonight, Elliott will
return to the San Antonio Spurs lineup as they host the Atlanta
Hawks. Elliott is only expected to play a few minutes, but the
return to the lineup will cap the end of a remarkable comeback.
(Denberg, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   BKN-ELLIOTT14 _ SAN ANTONIO _ Sean Elliott knows there are those
who worry about whether he can stand up to the rigors of the NBA
after undergoing a kidney transplant. The San Antonio Spurs forward
knows that two factions he must count on the most, his coach and
some teammates, are among them. He also knows something they may
not. There was the kidney transplant recipient who was kicked by a
horse. Another who was gored by handlebars in a motorcycle wreck. A
third who played college football. They took their shots. Their
kidneys survived. Now, Elliott will add one more person to his
list: himself. Some time after 7:30 p.m. today, the San Antonio
Spurs' forward will become the first athlete in professional sports
to return from a kidney transplant. (Rosner, Austin
American-Statesman)
</P>
