<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TEXBUDGET-TEX </SLUG>
 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Fort Worth Star-Telegram plans to move the following stories
for clients of the NYTimes News Service for AMs and PMs of Tuesday,
March 12, and thereafter. If you have any questions, please call
Lou Hudson, Paul Wagner or Jim Peipert on the Star-Telegram's
National/Foreign Desk at (817) 390-7785. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   L I F E S T Y L E &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   STAPLES-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Proverbs 22:6 says, ``Train a child in the way he
should go and when he is old he will not turn from it.'' I read an
interesting twist on that proverb recently in my study Bible and it
went something like this: ``Train a child in the way he should go _
and go there yourself once in a while.'' If you are wondering how
to have a moral and lasting effect on your children, that in
essence is the sum of God's advice to us. It is up to us to accept
it and apply it to our lives. By GRACIE BONDS STAPLES. Story has
moved in ``l'' lifestyle category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   C O M M E N T A R Y &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   RECORD-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ I fear that too often we take for granted the words of
those precious documents that guarantee our freedom: the
Declaration of Independence, the U.S. Constitution and the Bill of
Rights. You don't believe me? Let me tell you a sad tale. Several
years ago, a reporter in Madison, Wis., asked 112 people to sign a
petition that consisted exclusively of sections from the
Declaration of Independence and the Bill of Rights. Only one person
was willing to sign the petition. By PHIL RECORD. Story has moved
in ``k'' commentary category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   WRIGHT-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Each of America's great presidents had the courage of
his own convictions. Each had a passionate love for this country.
Each risked boldly. Each had a vision. The graceful patina of time
has polished their images, and history's sandpaper smoothed their
rougher corners. It would be unfair to measure today's candidates
against these icons. But not unfair to bear in mind that the office
itself deserves greatness. By JIM WRIGHT. Story has moved in ``k''
commentary category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
