<P>
   &QL; 
ROBB-COLUMN (Phoenix) - Notes and observations coming out of Super
Tuesday, including: There has probably not been anyone in American
political history less suited to be vice president than John
McCain. Can you imagine him loyally and effectively defending a
presidential policy with which he fundamentally disagrees? I
suspect George W. can't either. By ROBERT ROBB. Column moved in the
