<P>
   BC-HOUSE-CHAPLAIN-NYT (moved on Sunday, March 12)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Sunday, March 12,
about bitterness in Congress over the appointment of a Protestant
as House chaplain misidentified the medal under discussion for
Cardinal John O'Connor as a conciliatory gesture to Roman
Catholics. It is the Congressional Gold Medal, the body's highest
civilian honor. (The Medal of Honor is a military award.)
</P>
