<SLUG> BC-BOOK-AWARDS-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
CRITICS CIRCLE'S BEST FICTION PRIZE IS GIVEN TO `MOTHERLESS
BROOKLYN' 
</HEADLINE>
  (DUPLICATION NOTICE: Also filed in category `a') 
(js) 
 By JULIAN E. BARNES   
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ ``Motherless Brooklyn,'' a novel about a detective
whose Tourette's syndrome turns his sentences into rhymed barrages
